gomodel:SYNGO_1617  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: Xu et al generate syt-9-GFP KI mice and determine the subcellular localization of syt-9 protein by immunocytochemistry in brain sections derived from KI mice. The analysis reveals restricted expression of syt-9 primarily in the limbic system (hypothalamus, bed nucleus of stria terminals, septal area, medial amygdala), the basal ganglia (putamen, nucleus accumbens) and the pars reticulata in substantia nigra. Low, but detectable signals for syt-9 are localized to mossy fiber terminals in the hippocampus.\nCo-detection of synapsin I in the ICC approach reveals that all syt-9-GFP puncta are also positive for synapsin I, thus supporting the SV localization of the protein. Colocalization with MAP2-positive structures further supports the synaptic nature of the protein.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods (Neuronal Cultures and Lentiviral Infection)\nPrimary striatal neurons were isolated from newborn homozygous synaptotagmin-\n9 KI mice, dissociated by trysin digestion, and plated on\nPoly-D-lysine-coated glass coverslips (Maximov et al., 2007)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1617" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

